Is this really supposed to survive in mathlib once the file compiles?
Yes, the point is to check that this file does not import `Ring`.
Well, but I understand this while preparing the file. If it imports it, CI would give an error, no?

My understanding is that if someone adds an import to some other file at some later time, and this happens to end up with this file importing Ring, then we discover this before the import addition is merged.
